All Implemented Interfaces:
IStateSet<T,TracingStateSet<T>>
public class NFbyTracingSet<T extends INode<T>>
extends TracingStateSet<T>

Represents a set of "A never followed by B" synoptic.invariants to simulate, recording the shortest historical path to reach a particular state. This finite state machine enters a particular state (s2) when A is provided. If we are in this state when a B is provided, then we enter into a failure state.

Author:
Michael Sloan (mgsloan@gmail.com)
See Also:
NFbyInvFsms, FsmStateSet
